diff:1612572639:1612475505:=63,80d62%0a%3c #foxbegin 210206-005039-958360#%0a%3c (:div1 class=messagehead:)%0a%3c >>rfloat%3c%3c   %0a%3c [-05.02.2021 - 16:50-] &nbsp; %0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c (:if1 authgroup @tas:)%0a%3c >>rfloat%3c%3c%0a%3c {[foxdelrange button 210206-005039-958360 {$FullName} ]}%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c (:if1end:)%0a%3c !!!!!lauray%0a%3c (:div1end:) %0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c %0a%3c '''I think they can'''%0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c%0a%3c I grew up learning Chinese and English at pretty much the same time and though I generally find myself thinking in English, I feel like there have been times when I just think in Chinese. One odd example is that when I was learning Spanish I would find myself thinking in Chinese a lot. I've even accidentally spoken Chinese in Spanish Class because of this. I think this was probably because my mind connected a different language automatically to the other language that I knew which was Chinese. I feel like I think in Chinese when I'm consuming some sort of foreign show or trying to express myself in a way that English can't. Also when I'm speaking purely in Chinese sometimes I feel like I also think in Chinese. %0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c #foxend 210206-005039-958360#%0a
